Andreas Dräger is a PhD student at the [http://www-ra.informatik.uni-tuebingen.de Center for Bioinformatics (ZBIT)] in Tübingen, Germany. During his master thesis at the [http://www.uni-halle.de/MLU/index_e.htm Martin-Luther-University Halle-Wittenberg] he improved the storage of taxonomic information in BioSQL databases and implemented sequence alignment algorithms such as the Needleman-Wunsch- and the Smith-Waterman-Algorithm for global or local alignment, respectively.

